Notes: Environmental Tolerances: Does very poorly under low-N conditions like most grasses.
Soil Drainage: ["Somewhat poorly drained","Moderately well drained","Well drained","Well drained muck"]
Planting green: Utilizing a roller-crimper is suggested when planting corn into material greater than 12" tall as un-rolled cover may impact emergence.
Notes: Termination [Goal: Method: Timing: Flowering and freezing temps unlikely to co-occur.
Notes: Bloat risk and other animal health risks, similar to brassicas.
